rComments: Prof. Ashcroft is awesome! She is approachable and really interesting. I have taken two courses with her and loved both.

This professor presents as kind and helpful; however, when seeking guidance and/or further education she comes across as very condescending and is of the philosophy that the student should figure it out on their own. As such, she provides unhelpful comments and you are left feeling embarrassed you reached out for assistance in the first place.

If you want to learn, do not take any of her courses. It's bewildering that she taught 3 classes in the M&H stream. No wonder students have demanded that they completely rework the stream. There was no engagement from students because, quite simply, she is a terrible lecturer. Unapproachable & uninformed. Many of my peers have made similar comments
Approachable, understanding, easy to understand. Very nice professor! She gives excellent feedback. She's very interactive!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']
